  "body": "Output of `helm version`: 2.11.0\r\n\r\nSince #4221 was merged I started playing around with removing some of my internal `required` checks in CI and I noticed an interesting behaviour which I'm unsure if it is a bug or not.\r\n\r\nLooks to be due to it is allowing `nil` through unhindered which does not work great when doing something like `required \"API Token required\" .token | b64enc | quote`\r\n\r\nRunning `helm lint` against a template with `required` which then feeds into ` b64enc`:\r\n\r\n```\r\nhelm lint\r\n[INFO] Missing required value: API Token required\r\n==> Linting .\r\n[ERROR] templates/: render error in \"templates/secrets.yaml\": template: templates/secrets.yaml:9:77: executing \"templates/secrets.yaml\" at <b64enc>: invalid value; expected string\r\n\r\nError: 1 chart(s) linted, 1 chart(s) failed\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen I placed an empty string in values.yaml or did an inline `default` - note, it has to be done with `()` otherwise `required` throws about too many args or similar\r\n\r\n```\r\nhelm lint\r\n[INFO] Missing required value: API Token required\r\n==> Linting .\r\n\r\n1 chart(s) linted, no failures\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe other oddness is how the info message happens prior to `==> Linting`",
